== What are Macros? == <!--T:2-->

Macros are Python scripts that extend FreeCAD's functionality. They automate repetitive tasks, add new features, or create custom workflows. Stored as {{FileName|.FCMacro}} or {{FileName|.py}} files.

== Installing Macros == <!--T:3-->

=== Via Addon Manager === <!--T:4-->

# Go to {{MenuCommand|Tools → Addon Manager}}
# Select the "Macros" tab
# Browse or search for the desired macro
# Click "Install" and restart FreeCAD

=== Manual Installation === <!--T:5-->

# Download the macro file
# Place it in your Macro directory:
** Linux: {{FileName|~/.local/share/FreeCAD/Macro/}}
** Windows: {{FileName|%APPDATA%\FreeCAD\Macro\}}
** Mac: {{FileName|~/Library/Application Support/FreeCAD/Macro/}}
# Run via {{MenuCommand|Macro → Macros...}}

